ive transfer solution that takes into account the\nsystem geometry. We could reproduce the V348 Pav \\textit{B, V, R}, and\n\\textit{I} photometric and polarimetric data using a model with a WD magnetic\nfield of $\\sim28$ MG, a WD mass of $\\sim0.85$~M$_{\\odot}$ and a low\n($\\sim25^{\\circ}$) orbital inclination. These values for the WD mass and\norbital inclination are consistent with the measured radial velocities.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 2 Sep 2019 21:45:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-15"}
