{"id":"1909.00932","submitter":"Carlos Scarinci","authors":"Catherine Meusburger, Carlos Scarinci","title":"Lightlike and ideal tetrahedra","comments":"39 pages, 5 figures. Revised version","journal-ref":"Geom Dedicata 216, 26 (2022)","doi":"10.1007/s10711-022-00687-6","report-no":null,"categories":"math.GT math-ph math.DG math.MP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We give a unified description of tetrahedra with lightlike faces in 3d\nanti-de Sitter, de Sitter and Minkowski spaces and of their duals in 3d anti-de\nSitter, hyperbolic and half-pipe spaces. We show that both types of tetrahedra\nare determined by a generalized cross-ratio with values in a commutative 2d\nreal algebra that generalizes the complex numbers. Equivalently, tetrahedra\nwith lightlike faces are determined by a pair of edge lengths and their duals\nby a pair of dihedral angles. We prove that the dual tetrahedra are precisely\nthe generalized ideal tetrahedra introduced by Danciger. Finally, we compute\nthe volumes of both types of tetrahedra as functions of their edge lengths or\ndihedral angles, obtaining generalizations of the Milnor-Lobachevsky volume\nformula of ideal hyperbolic tetrahedra.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Sep 2019 03:14:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 25 Sep 2019 04:19:03 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 22 Jun 2020 01:31:23 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 28 Oct 2021 07:08:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-27"}
