er corotation\nradii than their strongly barred counterparts. Weak and strong bars have\nsimilar bar pattern speeds and rotation rates, which are all consistent with\nbeing fast. We did not observe any difference between the bulge prominence in\nSAB and SB galaxies, whereas nearly all the weak bars reside in the disc inner\nparts, contrary to strong bars. We ruled out that the bar weakening is only\nrelated to the bulge prominence and that the formation of weak bars is\ntriggered by the tidal interaction with a companion. Our observational results\nsuggest that weak bars may be evolved systems exchanging less angular momentum\nwith other galactic components than strong bars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Sep 2019 09:46:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-27"}
