he stars with the velocity of the underlying $^{13}$CO\nmolecular gas and report a mean difference of $0.04\\pm0.12$ km/s (with r.m.s.\nof 0.63 km/s) confirming that the stars and the gas are tightly coupled.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Sep 2019 12:43:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-09"}
